    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Daylight Saving Time IE encoding in EMM Information messages\n\n### Summary\nThe Daylight Saving Time information element in EMM Information messages was being incorrectly encoded as an LV (Length-Value) IE instead of a TV (Tag-Value) IE according to 3GPP TS 24.008. This caused interoperability issues with commercial UEs that expect the correct IE format.\n\nWhen the network sent EMM Information messages containing daylight saving time information, UEs would fail to parse the message correctly and ignore the entire information element. This was particularly noticeable when UEs were expecting network-provided time zone adjustment information.\n\nThe root cause was that the encode/decode functions were adding an unnecessary length octet and using incorrect length constants. The fix modifies the implementation to correctly handle the IE as a TV format, matching the specification and the behavior of similar IEs like TimeZone.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/DaylightSavingTime.c`: Removed length field processing from both encode and decode functions, simplified to TV IE format\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/DaylightSavingTime.h`: Updated MINIMUM_LENGTH from 3 to 1 and MAXIMUM_LENGTH from 3 to 2 to reflect correct TV IE sizing\n\n"
}